    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="388"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.00/1165.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Special Commissioner</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Puerto Cortes</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Dawson says Bertrand was elected first designate by Congress on this date;
                    that the Vice President was expected to arrive at the capital the following day;
                    and that many of the Government forces were retiring for the purpose of
                    disarmament. Adds that he will arrive in Washington March 19.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
